cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

The paper discusses support for film or television scriptwriting, which involves natural language processing and semantic analysis, suggesting that it belongs to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of mathematical algorithms for data clustering and display suggests that it could also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The mention of interactivity and collective, distributed problem-solving suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-categories.
